    • Method Detail

      • create

        IParameterInjector create(Class<? extends Annotation> annotationClass,
                          Object... parameters)
        Creates a new injector for the given annotationClass and parameters.

        Be aware: that for annotations with custom values you should always use create(Annotation, Object...), otherwise the injector won't be able to consider your custom values and will invoke all methods annotated with the given class. The only exception to this is InjectParameters, which will be recognized and checked for it's key.

        Note that each parameter will only be injected once per method.

        Parameters:
        annotationClass - The annotation class which marks the methods that should be invoked.
        parameters - The parameters that should be injected, in the order they should be injected.
        Returns:
        A new parameter injector.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - If any parameters are null or annotationClass is null.

      • create

        IParameterInjector create(Annotation annotation,
                          Object... parameters)
        Creates a new injector for the given annotation and parameters.

        Note that each parameter will only be injected once per method.

        Parameters:
        annotation - The annotation instance being equal to the annotations which mark the methods that should be invoked.
        parameters - The parameters that should be injected, in the order they should be injected.
        Returns:
        A new parameter injector.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - If any parameters are null or annotation is null.
        See Also:
        InjectParams for creating annotation instances.
